Class BoundedSortedMap<K,V>

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.AbstractMap<K,V>
      • java.util.TreeMap<K,V>
        • edu.ucla.sspace.util.BoundedSortedMap<K,V>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Cloneable, Map<K,V>, NavigableMap<K,V>, SortedMap<K,V>

    public class BoundedSortedMap<K,V>
extends TreeMap<K,V>
    A Map implementation that grows to a fixed size and then retains only a fixed number of the highest (largest) keys. All keys used in this class must implements Comparable.
    See Also:
    BoundedSortedMultiMap, Serialized Form

    • Method Summary

      V put(K key, V value)
